@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 14

title Network layer (L3): role and position

rectangle "L4 Transport\n(TCP/UDP)" as L4
rectangle "L3 Network\n(IP)\n(packets, routing)" as L3
rectangle "L2 Data Link\n(Ethernet/Wi-Fi)" as L2
rectangle "L1 Physical\n(medium)" as L1

L4 -down-> L3
L3 -down-> L2
L2 -down-> L1

note right of L3
  Typical functions:
  - hierarchical addressing (IP)
  - routing between networks
  - fragmentation (IPv4)
end note
@enduml
